{"id": "1407352797091069962", "channel_id": "1407352797091069962", "type": 0, "author_id": "237640529196744704", "author_name": "neolusso", "author_bot": false, "content": "First i want to say Congratulations on releasing the game in JP.\n\nNow onto the remark/suggestion . \nWe learned that the in the JP version there will be gameplay difference with GLB , honestly i don't think thats a good idea community wise , all currently available community ressource (guide,tier list and other) will be complitely worthless for the JP crowd and in the future JP made ressource will be useless to the GLB crowd , i feel like splitting the community is a really bad idea(they also have their own discord server ?!).It could just be like other gacha game , being 1/2 year(or less depending on update speed) late and just following a similar update schedule as the GLB version(or an accelerated one) that way JP and GLB players can communicate and relate.\n\nThanks for reading my concern about this segregation of community", "timestamp": "2025-08-19T13:17:34.177000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "☝️", "emoji_id": null, "count": 2}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407352797091069962", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Separation of GLB and JP", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1361169005435420785", "1361168939622727801"]}
{"id": "1407373877000142889", "channel_id": "1407373877000142889", "type": 0, "author_id": "1355724968956002314", "author_name": "xyakoto", "author_bot": false, "content": "Congrats on the official Japanese release.\n\nHowever, from what I can gather, the JP version of the game are vastly different from the global version.\nThis includes different character skills and enlightenments, different covenant effects, different relics and some boss has different mechanics, etc.\nThe differences are so huge that it's almost like running two different games, which I'd imagine is a huge workload increase.\n\nThus I have concerns about the game development going forward.\n\nDepending on how you guys allocate the work loads, I'm worried this might hugely impact the global version's development time. \n\nAs a matter of facts, there are already a lot of players share the thoughts of slow releases on new contents, and tendencies to neglecting old systems.\n\nSo please share with us more with your future plans on the matter. How do you plan to run two vastly different game versions at the same time. \nBetter yet: a road map of sorts.", "timestamp": "2025-08-19T14:41:20.019000+00:00", "edited_timestamp": null, "pinned": false, "mentions": [], "reactions": [{"emoji": "point", "emoji_id": "1356053112292511815", "count": 5}, {"emoji": "❌", "emoji_id": null, "count": 1}], "attachments": [], "embeds": [], "reply_to": null, "has_thread": false, "thread_id": "1407373877000142889", "flags": 0, "thread_title": "✅「Answered」Concerns about dev resources with the Japanese release.", "forum_channel_id": "1180845276823564288", "thread_tags": ["1181168197425172480", "1361169005435420785"]}
